Example minimal FastAPI main.py to drop in (paste & run)
# backend/app/main.py
from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File
from app.services.parser import extract_text_and_sections

app = FastAPI(title="ResumeGPT - MVP")

@app.post("/parse")
async def parse_resume(resume: UploadFile = File(...)):
    content = await resume.read()
    text, sections = extract_text_and_sections(content, resume.filename)
    return {"text": text, "sections": sections}
(Write extract_text_and_sections in services/parser.py using pdfminer + python-docx. Keep it simple at first.)

Scoring heuristics — implement these exact rules (no guesswork)
keywords_score = weighted match of exact_matches * 1.0 + semantic_matches * 0.6 divided by required keywords count → cap 40 points.

role_match = cosine(job_embedding, experience_embedding) scaled to 30 points.

experience_relevance = presence of role-specific metrics (regex count for numbers + % + words like "reduced", "increased") scaled to 20 points.

quality = heuristic (presence of action verbs, bullet length between 8–25 words, presence of metrics) scaled to 10 points.
Sum & normalize to 0–100.

Privacy & security rules you must enforce (solo, but non-negotiable)
Don’t store resume raw text by default. Keep ephemeral processing unless user opts in.

If you store anything, hash the filename and store minimal metadata.

Limit uploaded file size (e.g., 5 MB).

Validate file types (only pdf/docx/txt).

Avoid logging full resume content.

